definitions.definition: A genre of science fiction and art that combines fictional retrofuturistic elements with the technology , culture , and aesthetics of the period of history beginning in the interbellum between World War I and World War II and ending around the 1950s (known as the "diesel era" within the dieselpunk community).

main_definition: A genre of science fiction and art that combines fictional retrofuturistic elements with the technology , culture , and aesthetics of the period of history beginning in the interbellum between World War I and World War II and ending around the 1950s (known as the "diesel era" within the dieselpunk community).
